# Candy Break

React Native + Expo match-3 game. Portrait only. Bundle ID: `com.mike008.candybreak`.

## Architecture

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Types | `src/types/index.ts` | `PlayStyle`, `IGameShape`, board/cell interfaces |
| Constants | `src/constants/game.ts` | Grid size, scoring, `GAME_SHAPES`, `COLOR_POOL` |
| Engine | `src/utils/gameEngine.ts` | Pure logic: swaps, matches, cascades, specials, scoring |
| State | `src/hooks/useCandyBreak.ts` | Stage progression, mode rules, persistence, animations timing |
| UI | `App.tsx`, `src/components/` | Rendering, HUD, overlays, sounds |

Keep **game rules in the hook/engine**, not in UI. `App.tsx` only reads hook state and dispatches `tapCell`.

## Stage Model

A run = **5 levels** × **N stages** (one per `GAME_SHAPES` entry). Stages advance in `shapeIndex` order; after the last shape, `level` increments and `shapeIndex` resets to 0.

- `MAX_LEVEL`, `LEVEL_MOVES`, `LEVEL_GOAL_MULTIPLIERS` — difficulty scaling (`useCandyBreak.ts`)
- `SHAPE_GOALS[shapeIndex]` — base clear goal per stage (must match `GAME_SHAPES.length`)
- `initializeStage(shapeIndex, level)` — single entry point for board + mode-specific state

## Adding a New Play Style / Stage

Touch these files in order:

1. **`src/types/index.ts`** — extend `PlayStyle`; add optional fields on `IGameShape`
2. **`src/constants/game.ts`** — append to `GAME_SHAPES` with `id`, `label`, `mask`, `playStyle`, and mode config (`timerSeconds`, `bombRespawns`, etc.)
3. **`src/hooks/useCandyBreak.ts`**
   - Add matching `SHAPE_GOALS` entry (same index as `GAME_SHAPES`)
   - Extend `initializeStage` for setup (target color, frozen cells, timer, etc.)
   - Extend `tapCell` / `finalizeMove` for goal tracking, move consumption, win/loss, bomb spawn
   - Extend `ISavedGame` + save/restore if the mode has persistent mid-stage state
4. **`App.tsx`** — `bannerConfig` entry; update `fourthCard` HUD if the mode needs a custom stat
5. **`src/components/InstructionPage.tsx`** — add ko/en instructions for the new mode

Do **not** duplicate match/cascade logic in the hook — use `gameEngine.ts` exports.

## Play Style Reference

| Style | Goal | Moves | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|-------|
| `classic` | Clear N candies | Limited | Bomb at 60% moves left |
| `color-target` | Clear N of `targetColor` | Limited | Random target on init |
| `locked-tiles` | Thaw all frozen cells | Limited | 2 hits to thaw; goal = frozen count |
| `multiplier-rush` | Score threshold | Limited | Combo doubles multiplier (max 8×) |
| `bomb-storm` | Clear N candies | Limited | Bomb spawns at 30% moves; respawns |
| `timer-attack` | Clear N candies | Unlimited | Countdown timer; stars from time left |
| `shape-classic` | Clear N candies | Limited | Classic rules on a diamond-shaped board mask |

## Conventions

- Board uses `boolean[][]` masks; only playable cells participate in swaps/matches
- Candy colors: `Red`, `Blue`, `Gold`, `Mint` — assets in `assets/images/`
- Specials: 4-match → striped, 5+ → rainbow (engine handles spawn/clear)
- Scoring constants: `SCORE_BASE_POINTS`, `SCORE_EXTRA_TILE_POINTS`, `SCORE_COMBO_POINTS`, `BOMB_SCORE_BONUS`
- Persistence: `AsyncStorage` keys `bestScore`, `savedGame`, `stars_L{level}_S{shapeIndex}`
- Run `npm run typecheck` after changes; keep diffs minimal and match existing patterns
- OTA-safe changes only in JS/assets; native changes require new EAS build (`runtimeVersion` in `app.json`)
